[DONE] 42. GCP service account secret reader permission:
    - The local service account `gocd-agent-secrets@...` did not have `roles/secretmanager.secretAccessor`, causing `generate-env.js` to leave `<?secret?>` placeholders.
    - Switched to personal account (`gcloud config set account`), enabled `cloudresourcemanager.googleapis.com`, granted the role. This is a project‑level IAM binding – permanent, survives VM recreation.
    - Now `13.11` fills all secrets correctly, and the pipeline on the VM (which uses its own compute SA) already had the role.
[DONE] 43. Environment file generation from templates (13.11):
    - Created `templates/.env.staging.template` and `templates/.env.production.template` with section headers, comments, and `<?var?>`/`<?secret?>` placeholders.
    - Updated `generate-env.js` to accept `--template` flag, replacing placeholders with values from GitHub (for `<?var?>`) and GCP (for `<?secret?>`).
    - No defaults, no localhost fallbacks – missing values leave the placeholder and print a warning.
    - Menu option 13.11 automatically passes the correct template for staging/production; dev/docker remain unchanged.
    - Pipeline (`deploy.js`) also passes the template flag for staging/production, so remote `.env` files keep the beautiful structure.
[DONE] 44. Migration scripts rewritten to use template placeholders:
    - `migrate-environments.js` now reads the environment‑specific template and pushes only variables marked `<?var?>` to GitHub (no more keyword guessing).
    - `migrate-to-gcp-secrets.js` reads all templates and uploads only secrets marked `<?secret?>` to GCP (no more guessing based on `PASSWORD`, `SECRET`, `TOKEN`, `KEY`).
    - Both scripts use absolute paths resolved from `__dirname` so they work regardless of the current working directory.
[DONE] 45. VM tool‑readiness wait script redesigned:
    - Renamed `install-tools-on-vm.js` → `wait-for-vm-tools.js` to reflect its actual purpose (it no longer installs anything—the VM startup script handles all installations).
    - Replaced blocking `execSync` calls with non‑blocking `spawn` with timeouts so the loop never freezes under heavy CPU/IO.
    - Replaced log‑line polling with active readiness checks: `command -v docker && command -v node && command -v git`.
    - The script streams the startup log for visibility and exits the moment the tools are detected.
    - Removed all `apt-get install` commands from the script—the startup script is the single source of tool provisioning.
    - Updated `create-deploy-vm.js` and menu references to use the new filename.
[DONE] 46. VM provisioning time documented:
