[DONE] 65. Interactive SSH session fix:
    - Updated sshToVM.js to use `spawn` with `stdio: inherit` for proper terminal interactivity, and added error pausing to ensure connection issues are visible to the user.
[DONE] 66. Wrong Dockerfile target in build-and-push.js (PR #6):
    - Root cause: `build-and-push.js` specified `Dockerfile` instead of `Dockerfile.binary` for the web image.
    - Docker builds the last stage when no `--target` is given. The last stage in `Dockerfile` is `tunnel` (CMD `python tunnel.py`), not `web` (CMD `runserver`).
    - Result: The ghcr.io web image ran ngrok tunnel instead of Django, so port 8000 was never listening.
    - Fix: Changed `{ dockerfile: 'Dockerfile' }` to `{ dockerfile: 'Dockerfile.binary' }` in build-and-push.js line 118.
[DONE] 67. Stale cached images not updated on deployment (PR #6):
    - Root cause: `deploy.js` used `--pull missing` which only pulls images not already cached locally.
    - After the first deployment, even when the artifacts pipeline pushed a corrected image to ghcr.io, the old cached image on the VM was reused.
    - Fix: Changed `--pull missing` to `--pull always` in deploy.js so every deployment checks the registry for updated images.
    - Note: This reverts the optimization in item #40, but correctness takes priority over speed. The ~30s penalty is acceptable for deployment reliability.
[DONE] 68. VM resource exhaustion from mail container (PR #7):
    - Root cause: `mail-staging` (Poste.io) consumed 430% CPU and 382MB RAM (39% of total) on the 1GB e2-micro VM.
    - Symptoms: `docker ps -a` hung for 30+ seconds, load average 2.6/4.0/4.6, 40% IO wait from swapping.
    - Fix: Added `mem_limit` to all 10 services in docker-compose.vm.yml:
      - db-staging/production: 128m each
      - redis: 64m
      - mail-staging/production: 256m each
      - web-staging/production: 256m each
      - nginx-staging/production: 64m each
    - Total per profile: ~768m, leaving headroom for OS and Docker daemon on the 1GB VM.
[DONE] 69. Matplotlib font cache rebuild on every container start (PR #8):
    - Root cause: `setup-binary.sh` set `MPLCONFIGDIR=/tmp/.matplotlib`, which is ephemeral and wiped on every container restart.
    - Symptoms: "Matplotlib is building the font cache; this may take a moment" message delaying server startup.
    - Fix: Installed `fontconfig` + `fonts-dejavu-core` in Dockerfile.binary and ran `fc-cache -f` during build to pre-build the system font cache.
    - Set `ENV MPLCONFIGDIR=/app/.matplotlib` as a persistent path in the Dockerfile, and updated setup-binary.sh to use it.
    - System font cache is baked into the image layer; matplotlib's own cache persists within the container lifecycle.

[DONE] 70. Load Balancer & Path‑Based Routing Overhaul (humrine.com domain):
    - Problem: Multiple apps (Humrine, Badminton) needed to coexist under a single domain (humrine.com) using both sub‑domains and path‑based routing. The initial load balancer setup only supported subdomain‑based backends, leading to 502 errors on the root domain and "Not Found" on sub‑site paths.
    - Solution:
        * Created a self‑healing `setup-load-balancer.js` that idempotently inspects and corrects all components (instance group, health checks, backend services, URL map, HTTPS proxy, forwarding rules, firewall rules, DNS).
        * Added `certDomains` array to `loadbalancer.json` to generate multi‑domain Google‑managed certificates.
        * Implemented certificate versioning: new versioned certs are created and attached only after becoming ACTIVE, avoiding downtime.
        * Added `pathPrefix` support for backends, enabling routing like `/badminton-staging` and `/badminton-production` under the same host.
        * URL map now correctly creates a bare‑domain host rule with the correct default backend and exact/wildcard path rules.
        * Health checks automatically set the request path to `/prefix/` for path‑based backends.
        * Backend services are forced to HTTP and correct named port, even if manually misconfigured.
        * Firewall rules are now automatically created/updated for both health‑check probes (restricted sources) and actual traffic (0.0.0.0/0), with the correct `--rules` syntax.
        * Nginx templates in `badminton_court` repository were updated to strip the path prefix and include a 301 redirect for bare paths.
        * Environment variables (`WEB_HOST_PORT`, `NGINX_STAGING_HOST_PORT`, etc.) were added to avoid port conflicts between Humrine and Badminton containers on the same VM.
        * Menu options added: 6.32 List SSL certs, 6.33 Delete certs, 6.34 Monitor cert status, 6.35 Show active cert, 6.36 Cert domain status.
    - Result: All three sites (humrine.com, staging.humrine.com, app.humrine.com) and the two path‑based apps (/badminton-staging, /badminton-production) are now operational. The load balancer is fully self‑healing; running option 6.30 at any time corrects inconsistencies without downtime.

[PENDING] 71. Badminton Staging Nginx Placeholder Leak (502 on /badminton-staging)
    - Finding: The badminton nginx staging container repeatedly crashes because the generated config still contains the literal placeholder `__WEB_HOST_PORT__` instead of the actual port 8001.
    - Root cause: The `badminton_court` deploy script (`deploy.js`) reads `WEB_HOST_PORT` from the generated env file and uses the value to replace `__WEB_HOST_PORT__` in the template. However, the pipeline is not yet picking up the updated script.
    - Temporary fix: Manually wrote a correct config to the host file and recreated the container. Site works until next pipeline run.
    - Permanent fix: Commit the updated `deploy.js` (with `WEB_HOST_PORT` and `__WEB_HOST_PORT__` replacements) to the branch used by the staging pipeline and re‑run the pipeline.
    - Next: After pipeline success, verify https://humrine.com/badminton-staging/ loads and then proceed to Cypress testing.

